        "# Case Study: The Modulator Contrast\n",
        "### Evaluating Predictive Leverage and Sampling Volatility via Multivariate Normal Simulations\n",
        "\n",
        "**Author:** Morgan Polen  \n",
        "**Methodologies:** Joint Multivariate Normal Distributions, Ordinary Least Squares (OLS), Influence Diagnostics (Cook's Distance), Sensitivity Analysis, Post-Hoc Power Analysis.\n",
        "\n",
        "---\n",
        "\n",
        "## 1. Executive Summary & Core Objective\n",
        "In clinical data registries tracking complex chronic diseases, researchers frequently encounter weak, highly variable correlations between fundamental physiological biomarkers and macro-level functional outcomes. This project structures a synthetic patient simulation ($N=50$) mirroring these exact parameter constraints to evaluate a critical methodology question: *How vulnerable are small-sample clinical trials to individual high-leverage phenotypes, and how do we objectively identify them?*"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "GWtrWAzUpB2M"
      }
